WEBVTT

00:00.402 --> 00:01.642
<i>Previously on Cedar Cove...</i>

00:01.769 --> 00:03.520
Linnette: We should stay away from Gloria.

00:03.520 --> 00:05.177
He thinks that she's
stolen someone's identity.

00:05.177 --> 00:08.206
- I'm staying in Cedar Cove.
- Well, the job is here, in Seattle.

00:08.901 --> 00:10.517
You are on probation.

00:10.616 --> 00:13.127
If this case is not handled properly,
you will be out of a job.

00:13.192 --> 00:14.688
- She didn't come to work?
- Nope.

00:17.401 --> 00:19.168
The sheriff said that
because she's an adult,

00:19.170 --> 00:22.004
there's nothing they can do for 24 hours.

00:22.006 --> 00:24.673
What if she was kidnapped
or swept away in a flood?

00:24.675 --> 00:25.924
It's not raining out.

00:25.926 --> 00:27.943
Well, you're not ruling out kidnapping.

00:27.945 --> 00:29.244
Rebecca!

00:29.246 --> 00:30.846
Where were you?

00:30.848 --> 00:32.514
You disappeared, and you
didn't show up for work.

00:32.516 --> 00:35.450
- Paul was looking for you. He called.
- Several times.

00:35.452 --> 00:36.618
Yeah...

00:36.620 --> 00:38.053
I know.

00:38.055 --> 00:39.588
I missed two appearances.

00:40.457 --> 00:42.608
- I'm beat.
- No.

00:42.610 --> 00:44.158
Explanation. Now.

00:45.462 --> 00:47.638
Last night, I pulled
an all-nighter at work,

00:47.638 --> 00:48.477
and this morning,

00:48.636 --> 00:51.383
I had to drive all the way to
Brower County to file a motion

00:51.385 --> 00:53.035
to avoid a statute of limitations.

00:53.037 --> 00:54.319
On my way back, I was feeling tired,

00:54.321 --> 00:56.588
so I pulled off to the side of the road,

00:56.590 --> 00:58.006
and I closed my eyes for a second.

00:58.008 --> 00:59.608
I just woke up an hour ago.

00:59.610 --> 01:03.412
My phone was dead, and I had no charger.

01:03.414 --> 01:04.646
So, can I go now?

01:05.683 --> 01:09.017
- You're working too much.
- And too hard.

01:09.019 --> 01:10.919
Yeah, well, you can say, "I told you so,"

01:10.921 --> 01:12.254
but I'm going to go to bed.

01:12.256 --> 01:13.889
Excuse me.

01:17.878 --> 01:19.761
David won't budge

01:19.763 --> 01:21.430
on your working full time in Seattle?

01:21.432 --> 01:23.248
Not in the first year, no.

01:23.250 --> 01:25.300
He's a hands-on manager

01:25.302 --> 01:27.553
who apparently likes to
pop into the staff's office

01:27.555 --> 01:29.404
for brainstorming sessions, so...

01:30.624 --> 01:31.740
It's a great job.

01:33.260 --> 01:36.445
You're more important.
We're more important.

01:38.949 --> 01:40.265
You can't turn the job down

01:40.267 --> 01:43.291
just because it's going to be
hard for us to spend time together.

01:43.904 --> 01:46.029
- We'll have weekends.
- Yeah...

01:46.239 --> 01:48.322
until you have to prep
for a big court case,

01:48.324 --> 01:50.425
or I have a looming deadline.

01:52.228 --> 01:54.862
I have to ask you one more time...

01:55.832 --> 01:59.817
are you absolutely sure,
you support me taking this job?

02:02.105 --> 02:03.071
Olivia?

02:05.158 --> 02:06.874
Yes, Jack.

02:07.526 --> 02:10.193
Of course I support you taking this job.

